# Abby's Table — storefront environment
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (git-ignored) and fill in for live data. With nothing set,
# the storefront runs entirely on demo fixtures — no network, no tenant needed.
#
# Every variable here is SERVER-ONLY. None may be prefixed `NEXT_PUBLIC_`:
# that would bundle it into client JavaScript and publish it.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Data mode — demo | live
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# demo  the design-template fixtures. Deterministic, offline, no tenant.
# live  the real Aonik commerce API (requires the two variables below).
#
# Unset means DEMO in development — even with AONIK_API_URL set below. A dev
# server should not create real carts, place real orders or move real stock just
# because a connection string happens to be sitting in your .env.local. Live is
# something you ask for.
#
# Unset in PRODUCTION still means: live when AONIK_API_URL is set, demo
# otherwise. The failure modes are reversed there — a deployed storefront
# quietly serving fixture dishes and invented prices is far worse than one that
# refuses to start.
#
# Two ways to opt into live while developing:
#   1. set this to `live`, or
#   2. click the floating badge in the corner — it switches per-browser via a
#      cookie, no restart needed. That cookie is ignored entirely in production.
AONIK_DATA_MODE=demo

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Aonik connection — required for live mode
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Base URL, no trailing slash, and the API ROOT — not a /commerce prefix. The
# platform serves /commerce/... and /auth/token and /v1/registrations/... off
# the same root, so a prefixed base URL breaks identity.
#
# Local ports, verified against the Aonik repo:
#   https://localhost:5001  Aspire AppHost (src/Aonik.AppHost/AppHost.cs)
#   http://localhost:5049   standalone `dotnet run --project src/Aonik.Api`
AONIK_API_URL=https://localhost:5001

# The tenant GUID this storefront reads. Aonik partitions all commerce data by
# tenant and varies its shared caches on this header, so a base URL without a
# tenant is not a usable configuration — set both or neither.
#
# AbbysTable is ONE tenant of a multi-tenant platform (Aonik ADR-013): nothing
# in this repo may assume it is the only storefront Aonik serves.
AONIK_TENANT_ID=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Accounts — required for register / sign in
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The OAuth client the deployment's Keycloak issues storefront tokens for.
# POST /auth/token rejects a request without one, so without this the login and
# registration forms render their "accounts aren't available yet" state instead
# of failing in a way that looks like a wrong password.
#
# Two deployment prerequisites live outside this file (ADR-007):
#   - the realm must have the direct access (password) grant enabled; it is off
#     by default in Keycloak;
#   - Google sign-in, if wanted, is brokered in that same Keycloak. It is an
#     OPERATOR setting — a tenant cannot enable it for itself.
AONIK_AUTH_CLIENT_ID=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Deliberately absent
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# There is no AONIK_API_KEY. Aonik's storefront surface is anonymous — catalog
# reads take no credential at all, cart calls prove possession with a per-cart
# token, and customer calls use the signed-in session. A static service key
# would be both useless and a liability.
